    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "\n### Feature description\n\nI think this option somehow similar to `buflisted` and `buftype`. When it is set to `no` (like `nobufshada`), then buffer path wouldn't be saved to shada history (and hence wouldn't be presented in `:oldfiles` list).\n\n(Neo)vim already have option (flag `r` in `shada`) to prevent files from saving to shada history, but this is not enough: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12298.\n\nAlso such option will be more flexible, so it can solve https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/15195 (yes, it is already closed, but I think it's not implied solution) like this:\n\n    autocmd FileType gitcommit setlocal nobufshada",
